(1232, 102, 0, 0, 0, 'lion', 1, '2010-01-23 22:57:15', NULL, 426, 'Originally, the province of Manitoba was a square only 1/18 of its current size, and was known as the "postage stamp province".[49] Its borders were expanded in 1881, but Ontario also claimed a large portion of the land; the disputed portion was awarded to Ontario in 1889. It grew progressively, absorbing land from the Northwest Territories until it attained its current size by reaching 60°N in 1912.[49]', 2, '127.0.0.1', 0),
